00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,261
Ahhh!

278
00:12:11,298 --> 00:12:11,981
Shit!

279
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,300
I almost died.

280
00:12:14,090 --> 00:12:15,138
Wait for me!

281
00:12:15,156 --> 00:12:15,593
Ah!

282
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:16,270
Relaxing, right?

283
00:12:16,307 --> 00:12:17,267
Your muscles are so tight.

284
00:12:17,298 --> 00:12:17,981
Yeah.

285
00:12:18,018 --> 00:12:19,575
Now that I'm in my 30s,

286
00:12:19,606 --> 00:12:21,526
my body's really falling apart.

287
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,609
Are you already 39?

288
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,898
You're the same age as my dad!

289
00:12:26,923 --> 00:12:28,787
Shut up, I'm only 31!

290
00:12:28,818 --> 00:12:30,141
You already want me to be your dad?

291
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:32,129
Daddy.

292
00:12:32,147 --> 00:12:33,003
Hello, Daddy.

293
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,621
Don't let me see you guys getting old.

294
00:12:35,470 --> 00:12:38,966
Thanks for asking me
to work with you, Daddy.

295
00:12:39,450 --> 00:12:40,855
I'm only making you struggle.

296
00:12:41,370 --> 00:12:43,076
It's all blood and tears in our lives.

297
00:12:47,640 --> 00:12:48,640
Hey.

298
00:12:49,540 --> 00:12:51,827
Who's crying this late at night?

299
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,092
Did a ghost come to haunt us, To?

300
00:12:56,135 --> 00:12:57,135
Beer!

301
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:00,947
It's not some damn ghost.

302
00:13:01,670 --> 00:13:02,972
It's me crying.

303
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:04,381
Oh?

304
00:13:04,610 --> 00:13:05,610
Ki!

305
00:13:05,690 --> 00:13:06,690
Ki!

306
00:13:06,770 --> 00:13:07,784
What's wrong?

307
00:13:08,110 --> 00:13:10,141
Kae texted me to break up.

308
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,698
She dumped me!

309
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:15,033
I knew it.

310
00:13:15,058 --> 00:13:17,030
Long-distance relationships never work.

311
00:13:17,390 --> 00:13:19,107
She lives in Phang Nga

312
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:21,052
and you're out here
living like a dog in Bangkok.

313
00:13:22,170 --> 00:13:25,200
I'm going to go beg her
to get back with me.

314
00:13:25,690 --> 00:13:27,963
I know I've been working hard lately,

315
00:13:28,270 --> 00:13:30,664
but isn't breaking up over text too harsh?

316
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:32,953
It's okay.

317
00:13:32,984 --> 00:13:34,744
She said she wants to be alone.

318
00:13:34,763 --> 00:13:36,467
She doesn't want a relationship anymore.

319
00:13:36,492 --> 00:13:38,960
She's definitely cheating on me!

320
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,861
Why do you think that?

321
00:13:42,570 --> 00:13:44,972
I heard another guy's
voice when I called her.

322
00:13:45,003 --> 00:13:46,861
She said her gay friend came over.

323
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:48,806
That's bullshit.

324
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,424
I have gay friends.

325
00:13:50,443 --> 00:13:52,190
I know what they sound like.

326
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:54,873
That bitch!

327
00:13:56,264 --> 00:13:58,260
If you're sure she's cheating on you,

328
00:13:58,430 --> 00:13:59,526
then let's prove it.

329
00:14:00,350 --> 00:14:01,396
Prove what?

330
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:03,833
Prove that his girlfriend's
cheating on him.

331
00:14:03,864 --> 00:14:06,504
If she wants to break up with him,
at least give him a good reason.

332
00:14:06,930 --> 00:14:08,461
I'm not letting my bro get played.

333
00:14:10,210 --> 00:14:11,280
It's okay.

334
00:14:16,040 --> 00:14:17,310
Hey, that's enough.

335
00:14:18,830 --> 00:14:19,692
Hey.

336
00:14:19,704 --> 00:14:20,073
Hmm?

337
00:14:20,098 --> 00:14:21,098
That's enough.

338
00:14:21,910 --> 00:14:22,615
I'm going to take a shower.

339
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:24,750
No, don't go yet.

340
00:14:24,775 --> 00:14:26,258
I like your scent on me.

341
00:14:26,283 --> 00:14:27,858
It smells nice.

342
00:14:29,850 --> 00:14:31,649
Enough. I feel so sticky.

343
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:33,963
Don't go yet.

344
00:14:33,993 --> 00:14:36,430
We rarely get to spend time together.

345
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:37,760
Tonight,

346
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:42,843
I'm taking you on a
long flight with no transit.

347
00:14:42,861 --> 00:14:44,018
Enough.

348
00:14:44,043 --> 00:14:48,621
Tomorrow morning, I have to leave early
for a wedding in Phang Nga.

349
00:14:48,658 --> 00:14:50,058
I haven't even bought anything yet.

350
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:56,818
I might…

351
00:14:58,270 --> 00:14:59,670
not be able to go with you anymore.

352
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,273
Oh? Why not?

353
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:03,969
I've had this planned with you
since last month.

354
00:15:04,410 --> 00:15:06,898
I know I promised you,

355
00:15:07,370 --> 00:15:10,412
but my friend Meng needs help.

356
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:13,963
His wife has to have surgery on her uterus.

357
00:15:14,770 --> 00:15:16,203
He needs to stay with her,

358
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:18,498
so he asked to swap flights with me.

359
00:15:18,510 --> 00:15:19,950
I have to cover his flight.

360
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:21,120
But why you?

361
00:15:21,144 --> 00:15:22,704
Is there really no one else he can ask?

362
00:15:23,560 --> 00:15:24,800
There really is no one else.

363
00:15:25,410 --> 00:15:27,083
Remember your birthday?

364
00:15:27,530 --> 00:15:29,330
Meng agreed to swap
flights with me for that.

365
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,590
But I already told my parents
you're coming with me.

366
00:15:32,609 --> 00:15:35,347
I want to show off to my family
that my boyfriend is a captain.

367
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,003
I'm sorry,

368
00:15:39,430 --> 00:15:41,821
but my friend really needs help.

369
00:15:42,873 --> 00:15:44,870
It's not that I don't
want to meet your family.

370
00:15:45,450 --> 00:15:46,763
I really do want to meet them,

371
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:52,812
so I can try the Southern curry

372
00:15:52,830 --> 00:15:57,255
and see if the original flavor is as spicy
as what you just gave me.

373
00:16:02,190 --> 00:16:03,956
I won't break any more promises.

374
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:09,495
Mm. Don't ditch me again next time.

375
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:10,740
I won't.

376
00:16:18,630 --> 00:16:19,513
Wow, To.

377
00:16:19,544 --> 00:16:21,421
You bought an expensive bag
just for this trip?

378
00:16:21,800 --> 00:16:22,652
Expensive?

379
00:16:22,670 --> 00:16:23,846
I got this from in front of the foundation.

380
00:16:23,870 --> 00:16:24,570
It only cost a thousand baht.

381
00:16:24,572 --> 00:16:25,015
What?

382
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:25,470
Mm.

383
00:16:25,495 --> 00:16:26,495
Hold on.

384
00:16:27,273 --> 00:16:29,270
Wow, but this is a designer bag.

385
00:16:29,470 --> 00:16:30,000
Really?

386
00:16:30,380 --> 00:16:31,723
This must be a premium knockoff.

387
00:16:31,747 --> 00:16:33,827
I just thought the print looked nice,
so I bought it.

388
00:16:33,870 --> 00:16:36,123
To, you're handsome

389
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:37,230
and you have good taste.

390
00:16:37,510 --> 00:16:39,846
The only problem is
you're a little too broke.

391
00:16:39,864 --> 00:16:41,181
(Screw you.)

392
00:16:42,867 --> 00:16:44,860
Thank god I'm handsome.

393
00:16:44,904 --> 00:16:46,393
Yeah, yeah, you're handsome.

394
00:16:46,412 --> 00:16:47,113
Enough with the compliments.

395
00:16:47,138 --> 00:16:47,864
I need to take a shit.

396
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,230
Alright, let's go.

397
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:51,076
Shithead.

398
00:16:51,101 --> 00:16:52,129
Okay.

399
00:16:52,160 --> 00:16:54,492
I'll call you when I get there.

400
00:16:54,920 --> 00:16:56,246
(Safe trip.)

401
00:16:56,283 --> 00:17:00,209
(Next time, I promise I'll properly
introduce myself to your parents in person.)

402
00:17:00,570 --> 00:17:02,972
Hey, shouldn't you be
asking for my hand next time?

403
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,492
(I just might.)

404
00:17:04,966 --> 00:17:06,960
(Talk later. I have to work now.)

405
00:17:07,532 --> 00:17:08,910
Okay. Safe flight.

406
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:10,260
(Bye-bye.)

407
00:17:15,530 --> 00:17:16,530
Hey!

408
00:17:19,450 --> 00:17:20,129
Oh!

409
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:21,360
Hey!

410
00:17:21,630 --> 00:17:22,630
Whoa.

411
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,169
Mr. Boiling Tofu.

412
00:17:26,330 --> 00:17:27,889
Another hit-and-run, huh?

413
00:17:27,913 --> 00:17:28,941
Look who it is.

414
00:17:28,966 --> 00:17:30,916
It's the Stray-Dog Scammer.

415
00:17:30,947 --> 00:17:32,406
Don't you ever watch where you're going?

416
00:17:32,430 --> 00:17:33,932
Or did your brakes
fail again like last time?

417
00:17:33,956 --> 00:17:35,716
I was walking straight ahead.

418
00:17:35,741 --> 00:17:37,231
You're the one rushing off to
who knows where.

419
00:17:37,255 --> 00:17:38,476
What are you, a high-speed grandma?

420
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:40,713
Look, I know it was an accident,

421
00:17:40,990 --> 00:17:42,707
but do you even know how to apologize?

422
00:17:42,732 --> 00:17:44,153
It's basic manners.

423
00:17:44,196 --> 00:17:46,150
Didn't you learn proper manners in school?

424
00:17:46,178 --> 00:17:47,178
Seriously?

425
00:17:47,510 --> 00:17:49,846
Excuse me. Back in high school,

426
00:17:49,901 --> 00:17:53,606
I won the Lower Southern Thailand.
Good Manners Award.

427
00:17:53,636 --> 00:17:56,609
But I save my manners
for people with manners.

428
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:58,640
Are you sure you actually
competed in that contest?

429
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:01,070
Fine, I'm sorry.

430
00:18:03,780 --> 00:18:06,313
An apology like that? Just keep it.

431
00:18:07,850 --> 00:18:09,753
Then what do you want, huh?

432
00:18:09,990 --> 00:18:11,003
You wanna go one-on-one?

433
00:18:11,027 --> 00:18:12,027
Wanna go at it?

434
00:18:12,120 --> 00:18:12,658
Huh?

435
00:18:12,940 --> 00:18:14,590
Solving problems with violence?

436
00:18:14,621 --> 00:18:15,606
Barbaric.

437
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,403
Barbaric or not, you'll see.

438
00:18:17,427 --> 00:18:18,427
You're gonna cry.

439
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:19,981
Whoa.

440
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:21,156
Looks like we gotta charge in, bro.

441
00:18:21,169 --> 00:18:21,600
You wanna go?

442
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:22,880
Charge?

443
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:25,052
Oh, I'm definitely about to
let something charge out.

444
00:18:25,076 --> 00:18:26,430
Hurry up. I need to take a shit!

445
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:26,867
Oh?

446
00:18:26,886 --> 00:18:27,886
Alright.

447
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:31,920
Come on!

448
00:18:44,370 --> 00:18:45,378
Help!

449
00:18:45,815 --> 00:18:47,489
Help! Is anyone there?

450
00:18:48,630 --> 00:18:50,190
My door's broken!

451
00:18:50,550 --> 00:18:51,670
What's wrong with your door?

452
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,073
It's broken.

453
00:18:54,092 --> 00:18:55,803
It won't open.

454
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,384
Could you get someone to help?

455
00:18:57,427 --> 00:18:58,646
Hey, it's okay.

456
00:18:58,676 --> 00:19:00,295
I'm a rescuer. I'll help you.

457
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,640
But how are you going to do that?

458
00:19:03,630 --> 00:19:04,369
If the door's broken,

459
00:19:04,381 --> 00:19:05,692
then I'll just break it down.

460
00:19:05,729 --> 00:19:07,261
What? No!

461
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,664
Please just get someone else to help.

462
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,228
I don't want the door
slamming into my face.

463
00:19:10,252 --> 00:19:12,276
It's okay. I can save you.

464
00:19:12,301 --> 00:19:13,470
Step all the way back.

465
00:19:13,513 --> 00:19:14,566
No!

466
00:19:14,627 --> 00:19:15,760
Step back.

467
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:16,566
Trust me.

468
00:19:16,603 --> 00:19:17,680
I deal with this kind
of thing all the time.

469
00:19:17,704 --> 00:19:19,827
The door's going to hit my face. No!

470
00:19:19,852 --> 00:19:20,861
Step back, okay?

471
00:19:20,904 --> 00:19:21,606
Hey!

472
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:22,630
Step back!

473
00:19:36,620 --> 00:19:38,578
Sorry, I couldn't stop.

474
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:40,180
Are you okay?

475
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:44,300
Yeah.

476
00:19:44,540 --> 00:19:45,540
Thank you.

477
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:51,076
The lock's broken. It's all rusty.

478
00:19:51,095 --> 00:19:52,455
We should tell them to replace it.

479
00:19:54,170 --> 00:19:55,330
I'll make a complaint myself.

480
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,680
I have to go.

481
00:20:19,140 --> 00:20:20,252
Occupied!

482
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,206
Not you again.

483
00:20:37,255 --> 00:20:39,304
Didn't you see it was occupied?

484
00:20:39,329 --> 00:20:40,184
Why did you keep knocking?

485
00:20:40,209 --> 00:20:41,064
You have no manners.

486
00:20:41,101 --> 00:20:43,144
I saw it, but you were taking forever.

487
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:45,754
I thought you died in the toilet
and turned into poop particles in the air.

488
00:20:45,778 --> 00:20:47,470
I waited until the plane almost landed.

489
00:20:47,489 --> 00:20:48,972
Were you planning to never let anyone else
take a shit?

490
00:20:48,996 --> 00:20:51,138
Don't be dramatic. I
wasn't in there that long.

491
00:20:51,156 --> 00:20:53,046
You're messing with me on purpose.

492
00:20:53,520 --> 00:20:54,916
Don't flatter yourself.

493
00:20:55,300 --> 00:20:56,419
How did it even take you that long to poop?

494
00:20:56,443 --> 00:20:57,923
Did you eat an elephant or something?

495
00:20:58,020 --> 00:20:59,102
I have to use the bathroom after you.

496
00:20:59,126 --> 00:21:00,520
Is my nose going to stop working?

497
00:21:00,547 --> 00:21:01,450
Am I going to die?

498
00:21:01,489 --> 00:21:02,350
Gross.

499
00:21:02,381 --> 00:21:03,563
I only went in there to pee.

500
00:21:03,593 --> 00:21:05,015
There's no smell.

501
00:21:05,046 --> 00:21:06,553
If there's any smell,

502
00:21:06,572 --> 00:21:10,707
it's my expensive perfume.

503
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,000
Mm.

504
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:16,584
That smells more like funeral perfume.

505
00:21:16,615 --> 00:21:17,741
What are you talking about?

506
00:21:17,766 --> 00:21:19,740
It's amber wood.

507
00:21:19,772 --> 00:21:21,126
It smells seductively good.

508
00:21:21,610 --> 00:21:25,200
I bet all you smell every day is
roadside exhaust fumes.

509
00:21:25,243 --> 00:21:27,396
You should get your nose cleaned sometimes,

510
00:21:27,415 --> 00:21:29,790
so you can smell
something expensive like this.

511
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:32,295
Mm, then let me smell it.

512
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:34,449
I'm going to sniff your neck
and see how good it is.

513
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,400
Hey!

514
00:21:37,990 --> 00:21:38,990
Pretty tempting.

515
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,120
Tempting my temper!

516
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:43,883
Move!

517
00:21:43,907 --> 00:21:44,907
I'm going to take a shit!

518
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:56,086
PHANG NGA

519
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:57,600
I've arrived, Mom. I'm at the hotel.

520
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,421
Sure, I'm coming right over.

521
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,440
Mm.

522
00:22:02,770 --> 00:22:04,092
No f*cking way.

523
00:22:05,070 --> 00:22:06,246
Mom, I have to go.

524
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:07,283
See you at the wedding.

525
00:22:08,756 --> 00:22:09,756
What is this?

526
00:22:12,460 --> 00:22:13,975
This must belong to that punk.

527
00:22:13,993 --> 00:22:14,993
Ew!

528
00:22:15,260 --> 00:22:16,375
When did we swap bags?

529
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:18,873
Shit!

530
00:22:19,766 --> 00:22:21,846
This must belong to
that tofu-faced flight attendant.

531
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:23,090
Wow.

532
00:22:23,290 --> 00:22:25,021
These clothes and this watch.

533
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:26,996
This is all good stuff, bro.

534
00:22:27,132 --> 00:22:28,744
Yeah, he's right.

535
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,221
These are all authentic.

536
00:22:30,246 --> 00:22:31,772
Not premium knockoffs like yours.

537
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,723
How am I supposed to return this to him?

538
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,378
I don't even have his number.

539
00:22:35,409 --> 00:22:37,095
Then there's no need to rush.

540
00:22:37,340 --> 00:22:38,400
Can we borrow these?

541
00:22:38,436 --> 00:22:39,440
No way!

542
00:22:39,464 --> 00:22:41,243
That's basically stealing his stuff.

543
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:44,560
After all that public service,
don't you have any conscience?

544
00:22:46,340 --> 00:22:47,544
What the hell, Ki?

545
00:22:47,581 --> 00:22:48,609
Hey!

546
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:51,169
We're trying to go undercover
and catch Kae cheating.

547
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:54,781
I just need this for a quick disguise.
It'll be fine.

548
00:22:54,818 --> 00:22:55,975
Hell no!

549
00:22:56,030 --> 00:22:57,030
Take it off.

550
00:22:58,560 --> 00:23:01,987
Listen. Do you have money to buy us
the stuff we need for our disguise?

551
00:23:02,006 --> 00:23:03,006
Yeah.

552
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:04,270
Can I borrow 1,000?

553
00:23:04,980 --> 00:23:07,150
I forgot to bring my wallet.
Let me borrow 1,500.

554
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:10,467
Alright, idiots.

555
